    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="219"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72115/3227</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Swiss
                        Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sulzer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 49</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that between the
                    15th and 22d of December, 1917, there will arrive in San Francisco, Calif., 423
                    male German aliens, 18 German women and 13 German children who were removed from
                    the German merchant vessels in the harbors of the Philippine Islands. The
                    Government of the United States has considered it advisable to intern these male
                    alien enemies for the duration of the war but is unwilling at present to intern
                    the <pb facs="0311" n="227" xml:id="pg_227"/> women and children, provided they
                    are found to be admissible under the immigration law.</p>
                <p>Inasmuch as these women and children are presumably without means of support, I
                    desire to bring the matter to your attention, as in charge of German interests
                    in the United States, for such steps as you may be able to take towards
                    affording them relief, in order that they may not be left in a destitute
                    condition in San Francisco, Calif.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
